{
  "text": "However, trade liberalization would increase \u2026rms'output which has two contradictory e\u00a4ects on consumer surplus. Output increase, on the one hand, would directly raise consumer surplus, on the other hand, increases the stock of pollution which in turn reduces consumer surplus. Now, if inequality [CITATION_1] holds or in the other words h is small enough, pollution increment does not reduce the consumer surplus that much and consumers will bene\u2026t from output enlargement. But, we know that most of the time h is not su\u00a2 ciently small.",
  "citation_candidates": [
